This paper is about Neural Machine Translation (NMT), which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and falls under the Computer Science category. The paper describes a deep learning model for NMT, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of attention mechanisms, low-precision arithmetic, and sub-word units, which are all techniques commonly used in other deep learning subfields such as computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on translation benchmarks, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
